I know that NS doesn't support javascript, but would it be possible to have a workaround to handle a page containing only a location.replace script as in the example below. The site in question will work in netSurf but you have to manipulate the URLs yourself. Obviously a page like this could easily have a &lt;noscript&gt; section with a text link.

&lt;SCRIPT&gt;
location.replace\("/INGDirect.html?command=displayValidateCustomer&fill=1"\);
&lt;/SCRIPT&gt;

Netsurf Testbuild \(20 Apr 2007 19:15\) 
RPC with 64 + 16 + 2\(Screen\) MB 
ROS 4.39 

